<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1100,2063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<bibRefCitation author="Koorders, S. H." box="[136,436,1100,1127]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" pagination="169 - 180" refId="ref6462" refString="Koorders, S. H. (1919 [Mai] [24 October 1918]) Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Flora von Java No. 18. Beschreibung von Kalanchoe Schumacheri vom Idjen-Plateau und Revision der Crassulaceae von Java. (Mit 2 lithographischen Tafeln.). Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de Buitenzorg ser. 3, 1 (3): 169 - 180, Figures 14 and 15. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 205 / mode / 1 up (text); https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 243 / mode / 1 up (figures)]" type="journal article" year="1919">Koorders (1919: 169–170)</bibRefCitation>
stated: “Eine vergleichende Untersuchung der 2 bisher von 
<collectingRegion box="[1116,1166,1101,1127]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Java</collectingRegion>
bekannten Crassulaceae-Gattungen 
<taxonomicName box="[267,388,1136,1162]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[267,388,1136,1162]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoë</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[459,604,1136,1162]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,604,1136,1162]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hat mich zu der Ueberzeugung geführt, dass es Empfehlung verdient 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[136,281,1172,1198]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,281,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
als Gattung einzuziehen und mit 
<taxonomicName box="[668,789,1172,1198]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,789,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoë</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
zu vereinigen. Ein durchgreifender Unterschied zwischen diesen beiden Gattungen giebt es, soweit ich feststellen konnte, nicht, weil einige (ausserhalb 
<collectingRegion box="[1221,1271,1209,1235]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Java</collectingRegion>
vorkommende) 
<taxonomicName box="[136,257,1244,1270]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,257,1244,1270]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoë</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Arten bekannt sind, welche Kelchblätter besitzen, die bis zur Mitte mit einander verwachsen sind und dadurch einen natürlichen Uebergang bilden zu der Gattung 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[896,1041,1280,1306]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[896,1041,1280,1306]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, die sich nur durch einen bauchigkurzzipfeligen Kelch nur unbedeutend von 
<taxonomicName box="[629,750,1316,1342]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[629,750,1316,1342]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoë</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(im engeren Sinne) unterscheidet.” [English: “A comparative investigation of the two 
<taxonomicName box="[414,560,1352,1378]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Crassulaceae</taxonomicName>
genera hitherto known from 
<collectingRegion box="[895,947,1353,1379]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Java</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1081,1352,1378]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1081,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[1138,1283,1352,1378]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1283,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has led me to the conviction that it deserves recommendation to combine the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[922,1067,1388,1414]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[922,1067,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1252,1388,1414]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1131,1252,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As far as I could determine, there is no fundamental difference between these two genera, because some 
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1328,1424,1450]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis box="[1118,1239,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(occurring outside 
<collectingRegion box="[224,274,1461,1487]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Java</collectingRegion>
[an island in 
<collectingCountry box="[428,542,1459,1486]" name="Indonesia" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
]) are known that have sepals fused with each other up to the middle, and thereby form a natural transition to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[560,705,1496,1522]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[560,705,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which differs only insignificantly from 
<taxonomicName box="[1164,1285,1496,1522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1164,1285,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu stricto) by a bulbous, short-lobed calyx.”]
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1100,2063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<bibRefCitation author="Koorders, S. H." box="[189,438,1568,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" pagination="169 - 180" refId="ref6462" refString="Koorders, S. H. (1919 [Mai] [24 October 1918]) Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Flora von Java No. 18. Beschreibung von Kalanchoe Schumacheri vom Idjen-Plateau und Revision der Crassulaceae von Java. (Mit 2 lithographischen Tafeln.). Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de Buitenzorg ser. 3, 1 (3): 169 - 180, Figures 14 and 15. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 205 / mode / 1 up (text); https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 243 / mode / 1 up (figures)]" type="journal article" year="1919">Koorders (1919: 170)</bibRefCitation>
then formally includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[718,863,1568,1594]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,863,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1025,1568,1594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[904,1025,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when he states “Mit Einschluss von 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[136,285,1604,1630]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">Bryophyllum</taxonomicName>
[in 
<taxonomicName box="[333,454,1604,1630]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[333,454,1604,1630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]”, and in the key to the species of the entire island [“Arten der Gesamtinsel”] gives the rank of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[226,371,1640,1666]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[226,371,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, under 
<taxonomicName box="[458,579,1640,1666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,579,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as “Untergattung”, i.e., subgenus. This is regarded as 
<bibRefCitation author="Koorders, S. H." box="[1206,1451,1640,1666]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" pagination="169 - 180" refId="ref6462" refString="Koorders, S. H. (1919 [Mai] [24 October 1918]) Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Flora von Java No. 18. Beschreibung von Kalanchoe Schumacheri vom Idjen-Plateau und Revision der Crassulaceae von Java. (Mit 2 lithographischen Tafeln.). Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de Buitenzorg ser. 3, 1 (3): 169 - 180, Figures 14 and 15. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 205 / mode / 1 up (text); https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 243 / mode / 1 up (figures)]" type="journal article" year="1919">Koorders (1919: 170)</bibRefCitation>
having provided indirect reference to 
<bibRefCitation author="Salisbury, R. A." box="[565,749,1676,1703]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" refId="ref7171" refString="Salisbury, R. A. (1805 [1 June 1805]) The Paradisus Londinensis: or coloured figures of plants cultivated in the vicinity of the metropolis 1. William Hooker, No. 6, Frith Street, city not stated, presumably London, 157 pp. &amp; 117 plates. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 113616  page / 1 / mode / 1 up]" type="book" year="1805">Salisbury (1805</bibRefCitation>
: t. 3), where the genus name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[1084,1229,1676,1702]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1229,1676,1702]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[136,354,1712,1739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" refId="ref8136" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. [Regnum Vegetabile 159]. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal volume" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[231,280,1712,1738]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 41.4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1100,2063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<bibRefCitation author="Koorders, S. H." box="[189,437,1748,1774]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" pagination="169 - 180" refId="ref6462" refString="Koorders, S. H. (1919 [Mai] [24 October 1918]) Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Flora von Java No. 18. Beschreibung von Kalanchoe Schumacheri vom Idjen-Plateau und Revision der Crassulaceae von Java. (Mit 2 lithographischen Tafeln.). Bulletin du Jardin Botanique de Buitenzorg ser. 3, 1 (3): 169 - 180, Figures 14 and 15. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 205 / mode / 1 up (text); https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 27173  page / 243 / mode / 1 up (figures)]" type="journal article" year="1919">Koorders (1919: 170)</bibRefCitation>
additionally recognised the subgenus ‘ 
<emphasis box="[886,905,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<emphasis box="[990,1136,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Eukalanchoe</emphasis>
’, 
<emphasis box="[1162,1283,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">nom. inval</emphasis>
., i.e., 
<emphasis box="[1356,1375,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,257,1784,1810]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,257,1784,1810]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, epithets for subdivisions of a genus may not consist of the name of the genus with the prefix “ 
<emphasis box="[148,179,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Eu</emphasis>
-” and a subdivision of a genus that includes the 
<typeStatus box="[740,788,1821,1847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
of the genus must repeat the name of the genus unaltered (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[143,363,1856,1883]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" refId="ref8136" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. [Regnum Vegetabile 159]. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal volume" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[240,289,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 21.3 and Ex. 3, and Articles 22.1 and 22.2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1100,2063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
When treated as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[561,682,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[561,682,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the nomenclature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[943,1088,1892,1918]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[943,1088,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, i.e., as 
<emphasis box="[1192,1211,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
