<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,441,266,292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Nomenclatural notes</emphasis>
:—Note that 
<bibRefCitation author="Wickens, G. E." box="[593,821,266,292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref8518" refString="Wickens, G. E. (1987) Crassulaceae. In: Polhill, R. M. (Ed.) Flora of Tropical East Africa: Crassulaceae. Published on behalf of the East African Governments by A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, pp. 1 - 66." type="book chapter" year="1987">Wickens (1987: 27)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authority="Vest (1820: 409)" authorityName="Vest" authorityPageNumber="409" authorityYear="1820" box="[939,1314,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Physocalycium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[939,1109,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Physocalycium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vest, L. C. von" box="[1118,1314,266,293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" pagination="397 - 410" refId="ref8295" refString="Vest, L. C. von (1820 [14 July]) I. Aufsatze. Botanische Bemerkungen. Von Hrn. Prof. Dr. v. Vest. Physocalycium?. Flora; oder, (allgemeine) Botanische Zeitung. Regensburg, Jena 3, 2 (26): 397 - 410." type="journal article" year="1820">Vest (1820: 409)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1329,1445,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">nom. illeg</emphasis>
. (
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[143,375,302,329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" refId="ref8136" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. [Regnum Vegetabile 159]. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal volume" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[244,298,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 52.1) in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[754,899,302,328]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,899,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vest" authorityYear="1820" box="[1037,1206,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Physocalycium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1206,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Physocalycium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Andrews" authorityName="Andrews" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Vereia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crenata">
<emphasis box="[1285,1452,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Vereia crenata</emphasis>
Andrews
</taxonomicName>
(1798: t. 21), a synonym of the African 
<taxonomicName authority="(Andrews) Haworth (1812: 109)" authorityName="Haworth" authorityPageNumber="109" authorityYear="1812" baseAuthorityName="Andrews" box="[685,1172,338,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Vereia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crenata">
<emphasis box="[685,802,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K. crenata</emphasis>
(Andrews) 
<bibRefCitation author="Haworth, A. H." box="[934,1172,338,364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" refId="ref6287" refString="Haworth, A. H. (1812) Synopsis plantarum succulentarum, cum descriptionibus, synonymis, locis; observationibus anglicanis, culturaque. [Kalenchoe, sic. Kalanchoe, on pp. 109 - 110; Bryophyllum p. 110.] Typis Richardi Taylor et Socii, Shoe-Lane, Londoni, 334 pp.; including ' Appendix'. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 38208  page / 118 / mode / 1 up]" type="book" year="1812">Haworth (1812: 109)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the only element having been included, is representative of 
<emphasis box="[528,547,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName box="[628,749,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[628,749,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vest" authorityYear="1820" box="[763,933,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Physocalycium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[763,933,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Physocalycium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
therefore does not belong in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[136,281,410,436]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,281,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or in that of 
<emphasis box="[433,452,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[533,678,410,436]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[533,678,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for that matter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
Some species better accommodated in 
<emphasis box="[629,648,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[731,876,446,472]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[731,876,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were previously included in 
<taxonomicName box="[1206,1324,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kitchingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1324,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kitchingia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1339,1444,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">pro parte</emphasis>
, excluding type, and in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker) Boiteau (1947: 7)" authorityName="Boiteau" authorityPageNumber="7" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[390,991,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Kitchingia">
<emphasis box="[390,511,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[576,694,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kitchingia</emphasis>
(Baker) Boiteau (1947: 7)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1003,1106,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">pro parte</emphasis>
, excluding type. The 
<typeStatus box="[1349,1452,482,508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[166,284,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kitchingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[166,284,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kitchingia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker (1881: 268)" authorityName="Baker" authorityPageNumber="268" authorityYear="1881" box="[317,769,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kitchingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracilipes">
<emphasis box="[317,555,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kitchingia gracilipes</emphasis>
Baker (1881: 268)
</taxonomicName>
, which was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, G. F. &amp; Figueiredo, E." box="[1069,1447,518,545]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" pagination="162 - 172" refId="ref7466" refString="Smith, G. F. &amp; Figueiredo, E. (2018 a) The infrageneric classification and nomenclature of Kalanchoe Adans. (Crassulaceae), with special reference to the southern African species. Bradleya 36: 162 - 172. https: // doi. org / 10.25223 / brad. n 36.2018. a 10" type="journal article" year="2018">Smith &amp; Figueiredo (2018a: 169)</bibRefCitation>
; its currently accepted name is 
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker) Baillon (1885: 469)" authorityName="Baillon" authorityPageNumber="469" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[476,1040,554,581]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracilipes">
<emphasis box="[476,716,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kalanchoe gracilipes</emphasis>
(Baker) Baillon (1885: 469)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="89" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,590,616]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—Species and infraspecific taxa included in 
<emphasis box="[831,850,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[936,1081,590,616]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1081,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and nothospecies derived from intra-subgenus hybridisation generally have a perennial, biennial, or short-lived multiannual 
<emphasis box="[1217,1306,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">lifespan</emphasis>
, with plants being 
<emphasis box="[204,317,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">terrestrial</emphasis>
and ± 
<emphasis box="[390,519,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">herbaceous</emphasis>
to 
<emphasis box="[552,703,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">brittle-woody</emphasis>
. Representatives of 
<emphasis box="[928,947,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[1025,1170,662,688]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1025,1170,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from taxa included in other subgenera recognised in 
<taxonomicName box="[505,626,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,626,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by variously developing 
<emphasis box="[909,985,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">bulbils</emphasis>
on the leaf blade margins, typically at the indentations between crenations or teeth, i.e., they are 
<emphasis box="[747,968,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">phyllo-bulbiliferous</emphasis>
(not observed in the case of 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker (1887: 472)" authorityName="Baker" authorityPageNumber="472" authorityYear="1887" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="streptantha">
<emphasis box="[1292,1452,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K. streptantha</emphasis>
Baker (1887: 472)
</taxonomicName>
[see 
<bibRefCitation author="Figueiredo, E. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[412,771,770,797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" pagination="32 - 54" refId="ref5901" refString="Figueiredo, E. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2021) An overview of plant collecting in Angola from 1690 to 2000. Phytotaxa 523 (1): 32 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 523.1.2" type="journal article" year="2021">Smith &amp; Figueiredo 2021: 199</bibRefCitation>
]); by having tetramerous 
<emphasis box="[1068,1150,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">flowers</emphasis>
that are usually distinctly pendulous at anthesis; by the 
<emphasis box="[474,544,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">sepals</emphasis>
usually being substantially fused into a conspicuous tube; a 
<emphasis box="[1237,1373,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">corolla tube</emphasis>
that is often substantially obscured by the 
<emphasis box="[532,645,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">calyx tube</emphasis>
, especially lower down at the level of the 
<emphasis box="[1116,1198,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">carpels</emphasis>
; by having the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">corolla tube</emphasis>
indented-constricted ± above the 
<emphasis box="[558,640,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">carpels</emphasis>
so often giving it a bulbous appearance; by the 
<emphasis box="[1165,1268,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">filaments</emphasis>
being ± inserted in the lower ⅓ of the corolla tube and often being adnate to the corolla very low down; by the 
<emphasis box="[1178,1262,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">anthers</emphasis>
being ± exserted or at least distinctly visible at the mouth; by having four 
<emphasis box="[764,867,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">filaments</emphasis>
of two similar lengths; by having the carpels shorter than the styles; and by having 
<emphasis box="[490,639,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">nectar scales</emphasis>
that are generally wider than long. Several representatives of 
<emphasis box="[1356,1375,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">K</emphasis>
. subg. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1805" box="[136,281,1022,1048]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,281,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have 
<emphasis box="[345,845,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">developed multiple reproductive mechanisms</emphasis>
and have a tendency to become 
<emphasis box="[1200,1451,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">naturalised and weedy</emphasis>
in places well separated from their natural distribution ranges in 
<collectingCountry box="[859,994,1058,1084]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, G. F. &amp; Shtein, R. &amp; Klein, D. - P. &amp; Parihar, B. &amp; Almeida, A. &amp; Rodewald, S. &amp; Kadereit, G." box="[1009,1221,1058,1085]" pageId="2" pageNumber="89" pagination="2 - 22" refId="ref7939" refString="Smith, G. F., Shtein, R., Klein, D. - P., Parihar, B., Almeida, A., Rodewald, S. &amp; Kadereit, G. (2021 c) Sexual and asexual reproduction in Kalanchoe (Crassulaceae): a review of known and newly recorded strategies. Haseltonia 28: 2 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.2985 / 026.028.0101" type="journal article" year="2021">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[1085,1134,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="89">et al</emphasis>
. 2021c
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
